==German==
===Schale (1)===
====Etymology====
From {{OHG.}} ''skala'', possibly from Germanic ''*skelo'' "cup made from a [[skull]]"; compare Norwegian [[skål]]. Related to ''[[scale]]'' (balance) and ''[[shell]]''.
====Noun====
'''Schale''' ''f'' (''pl'' Schalen)
# [[bowl]], [[cup]]

====Related terms====
*[[Schalentier]]
*[[Schalenwild]]
*[[verschalen]]
*[[sch&auml;len]]

===Schale (2)===
====Etymology====
Related to ''[[scale]]'' (eg. of a fish).
====Noun====
'''Schale''' ''f'' (''pl'' Schalen)
# [[husk]]
